    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe underline color is replaced by the foreground color when underneath the floating window.\n\n<img width=\"374\" height=\"227\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/06227797-ea19-4a79-b510-ae477088863b\" />\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create `minimal.lua`:\n```lua\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf, 0, -1, false, { \"Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet\" })\n\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"RedUnderline\", { underline = true, sp = \"#ff0000\" })\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"red_underline\")\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(buf, ns, 0, 0, {\n    end_col = 26,\n    hl_group = \"RedUnderline\",\n})\n\nlocal float_buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\nlocal win = vim.api.nvim_open_win(float_buf, false, {\n    relative = 'editor',\n    row = 0,\n    col = 12,\n    width = 15,\n    height = 3,\n    style = 'minimal',\n})\nvim.api.nvim_set_option_value('winblend', 50, { win = win })\n```\n2. Run `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe underline should display the correctly blended color when underneath the floating window\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-726+ga69f2db773\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nHaven't tried\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
